question_title: Will the interest in “opm” change between 2026-02-04 and 2026-02-15 according to Google Trends?
summary: Google Trends interest in "opm" spiked to 100 on Jan 26 during the government shutdown, which ended Feb 4. The question compares Feb 4 (Wednesday, ~15) to Feb 15 (Sunday). Historical data shows weekend values average ~6 points lower than weekdays, exceeding the ±3 threshold. However, the DHS funding deadline on Feb 13 creates uncertainty - another shutdown or crisis could spike interest. DECREASE is most likely due to the weekend effect and post-shutdown decay, but INCREASE has meaningful probability if DHS negotiations fail.

factors.description: Weekend effect: Feb 15 is Sunday vs Feb 4 Wednesday. Historical weekend values average 8.8 vs weekday 15.2 (~6 point drop), exceeding the ±3 threshold.
Post-shutdown decay: Jan 26 spike (100) has been steadily declining. Shutdown ended Feb 4, removing the primary search driver.
DHS funding deadline Feb 13: Another potential shutdown/news cycle just 2 days before resolution. Negotiations remain contentious.
Political volatility: Ongoing DHS funding fight, immigration policy disputes could generate news that drives OPM searches.
